1)to display hidden files
ls -a

2)to change all extention type
rename -v 's/.txt/.htm/' *.txt


3)to create link file
ln -s demo1.txt textlink.txt

4)to crete hard link
ln demo2.txt hardlink.txt


6)modify time stamp of file 
touch -t 202006291512 demo3.txt

7)crate file using touch
touch abc.txt

8)print all lines exclude first 5 lines
tail -n +6 number.txt


11)to see current user
 whoami
 
12)find current terminal
tty

15) Find all users logged into the system 
users


16)Find all users logged in and terminals in use
who

17)Find a given word/pattern from the file
i) grep "ap" test.txt
ii) fgrep "name" test.txt
iii) egrep "nam+e" test.txt


18)make the files read only
chmod 444 demo1.txt	//444

19)Make a file as write, read and execute
chmod 777 demo1.txt

20)Take input from the file, count words and store output to other file
wc < number.txt > numbercount.txt

21)Count words in output of “who” command
who | wc


22)Print lines 5 to 10 from the given file
head  number.txt | tail -n +5

23)Print the uniq values from the unsorted file
sort -n unsorted.txt | uniq


25) 
ls -S

28)Convert file contents into uppercase , also learn "-s" option of this command
cat test.txt | tr "a-z" "A-Z"

